{"word":"ἀπομύσσω","slug":"ἀπομύσσω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπομύσσω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to wipe</i> the nose, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>:— <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to blow one's nose</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to make</i> him <i>sharp, sharpen</i> his <i>wits</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> Horace's <i>vir emunctae naris</i>.<p/></div>"}]}